+--------------------------------------------------------------------+  00001000
|  MAILER General Commands:                                          |  00002000
|                                                                    |  00003000
|  CHECK - Check if another user has mail (not yet implemented).     |  00004000
|                                                                    |  00005000
|  FORWARD - Deliver mail to a userid other than the one specified   |  00006000
|            in the headers.  It is legal to forward mail to more    |  00007000
|            than 1 address.  If you want to continue to receive     |  00008000
|            a copy of the mail at your userid, add a forward with   |  00009000
|            an address of '<*>'.                                    |  00010000
|                                                                    |  00011000
|      FORWARD ADD    destaddr                                       |  00012000
|              DELETE destaddr | ALL                                 |  00013000
|              LIST                                                  |  00014000
|                                                                    |  00015000
|  HELP | ? - Get list of commands.                                  |  00016000
|                                                                    |  00017000
|  SHOW <show-options>  - Display assorted counters, etc.            |  00018000
|                                                                    |  00019000
|  show-options:                                                     |  00020000
|                                                                    |  00021000
|    STATUS                                                          |  00022000
|     Various Mailer status variables are returned.  These are:      |  00023000
|     Since: <date time> - time of last Mailer restart.              |  00024000
|     Msgs in/out: Number of messages (mail) received and sent.      |  00025000
|     Max Multi:  Maximum number of recipients for a single message. |  00026000
|     Stack Max:  Percentage Mailer internal storage utilization.    |  00027000
|                                                                    |  00028000
|    DOMAINS <domain-name>                                           |  00029000
|     Statistics on outgoing files to other domain Mailers.          |  00030000
|                                                                    |  00031000
|    INCOMING <nodename> <userid>                                    |  00032000
|     Statistics on files received from other network Mailers.       |  00033000
|                                                                    |  00034000
|    OUTGOING <hostname>                                             |  00035000
|     Statistics on outgoing files to other network Mailers.         |  00036000
|                                                                    |  00037000
|    SPECIAL <userid>                                                |  00038000
|     Statistics on mail to special userids (i.e. SYSTEM).           |  00039000
|                                                                    |  00040000
|  SMSG - Used as a prefix to other commands causes the reply to     |  00041000
|  be sent as a machine-readable SMSG.                               |  00042000
|                                                                    |  00043000
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+  00044000
